      "playtime_at_review": 153,
      "review_text": "This was really fun! I love that the body parts are configured using sliders, and that you can apply multiple coat/skin patterns. I recreated a couple Neopets and got a cool random-generated creature. I hope in the future we get even more options to choose from.",
      "timestamp_created": 1773888642
    },
    {
      "review_id": "221133519",
      "author_steamid": "76561198045443025",
      "voted_up": true,
      "votes_up": 1,
      "playtime_at_review": 15,
      "review_text": "such a detailed, cute, easy to use and fun character creator! so many sliders... so much potential for creatures...",
      "timestamp_created": 1773998844
    },
    {
      "review_id": "221143988",
      "author_steamid": "76561198307149904",
      "voted_up": true,
      "votes_up": 1,
      "playtime_at_review": 230,
      "review_text": "A character creator so fun and whimsical I bought it twice to support the dev, once on itch.io and once here! Itch even gives you a steam key so I gave that to a friend to spread the whimsy. It's criminally underrated and I really really hope it gets all the attention it deserves someday. It's like mii maker except better, you can even throw your creatures around like ragdolls and who doesn't want to throw their beloved characters around??\n\nI have a few wishes and very minor qol gripes (notably more options for asymmetry like mismatched eye colours, a way to quickly centre sliders and a more consistent custom colour picker) but it's already extremely flexible and well worth your money if you enjoy this kind of thing. The demo alone is already excellent and it only gets 10x better in the full game. Please consider picking it up if you can, the dev deserves it!!",
      "timestamp_created": 1774006387
    },
    {
      "review_id": "221202095",
